flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Periodic category sourcing window or event-driven signal (high spend cadence, forecasted demand surge, supplier risk alert, or contract expiration) detected in planning or ERP systems.]
  A --> N1[Stream: DDM/Crawlers + STREAMS - Consolidate spend, contracts, forecasts, inventory and supplier risk data into the data foundation]
  N1 --> N2[Cortex: Cortex RCA Service + Cortex Auto Forecast - Run analytics: demand signals, supplier risk scoring, contract rule matching, and market benchmarking]
  N2 --> N3{Agent: Agent Team (agentic_ai) orchestrated by Process Builder - Agentic AI recommends sourcing route and supplier shortlist, including contract-aware negotiation plan and PO timing}
  N3 -->|Primary| N4[PB: Process Builder (Transaction + Remote Functions) - Automate RFx/RFP creation, contract checks, and schedule negotiation/PO timing; create action items for sourcing team]
  N4 --> N5[PB: CWB Lifecycle - Human-in-the-loop approval and exception handling for high-impact awards or overrides]
  N5 --> N6[PB: UI Screen + Notification - Notify stakeholders and surface sourcing plan, savings estimate, and working-capital impact on UI/dashboard]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Reduced COGS (target 2–5%), preserved/expanded margins, improved supplier resilience and reduced supply risk, shortened sourcing cycle times, and optimized working capital via contract-aligned PO timing and smarter payment terms.]
  N3 -->|Supplier risk score above acceptable ...| B1[Agentic AI routes opportunity to strategic sourcing & supplier development subprocess (larger due diligence, capacity validation) and excludes from open auction.]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Longer cycle time but reduced supply and financial risk; higher confidence in supplier selection.]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Urgent shortfall / expedited demand w...| B2[Agent recommends rapid RFP or buy-now direct negotiation with premium terms; Process Builder triggers expedited approval path and Kinaxis expediting workflows.]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Faster fulfillment at higher procurement cost; prioritized allocation and minimized service disruptions.]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Commodity, high-volume, low-risk cate...| B3[Agent recommends open auction (e-auction) with automated bid evaluation and contract templating.]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Maximized supplier competition, faster cycle, higher probability of achieving lower COGS.]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]